pageContext.claim: “And the skyrocketing cases in Europe have shown draconian lock downs, and that's what they are, they're draconian, do not stop the virus.”
pageContext.analysis: Unlike the United States, Europe managed to crush its first wave and was fairly open over the summer. Then the second wave came sooner in Europe than in the United States, requiring new restrictions, but the USA quickly caught up after the November election.
